                  <summary>Apollonios approves the distribution of Milesian wool to the slave-girls in Memphis, and tells Zenon to give orders to let them have as much as they need.  The wool came from a flock of Milesian sheep which Apollonios owned in the Fayoum and the girls were employed in a wool factory beloning to him in Memphis.</summary>
